FBIS4-35770 "drnes107_n_94015" FBIS-NES-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 LEBANON Hizballah Promises Retribution for Assault Hizballah Promises Retribution for Assault Fadlallah, Others React NC0206164994 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1600 GMT 2 Jun 94 NC0206164994 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Excerpts] Shaykh Muhammad Mahdi Shams al-Din has affirmed that despite the occupation enemy's spiteful methods and aggression, the resistance will continue to forge ahead with its confrontation of the occupation. He urged those in charge of the international order to end the Israeli occupation of Lebanon. Acting Mufti Shaykh Muhammad Rashid Qabbani has urged the Arabs and the world to put an end to the Jewish acts of belligerence, which will trigger further conflicts and a state of instability in this world. [passage omitted] 'Allamah Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah said: We decided that there is no place for Israel among us. The battle [against Israel] will be as wide as the world so that the usurpers will leave our land. Fadlallah criticized the United States, describing it as the wolf that devours man, peace, and life. Fadlallah held the United States responsible for the Israeli attacks. Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah stressed the determination to continue struggle and jihad.
